## Component Conversion Patterns

### 1. Basic Function Component → Volt Inline Component

**React:**

```jsx
function Counter() {
    const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

    return (
        <div>
            <p>Count: {count}</p>
            <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Increment</button>
        </div>
    );
}
```

**Volt Inline (functional style):**

```php
<?php
use function Livewire\Volt\{state, computed};

state(['count' => 0]);

$increment = fn() => $this->count++;
?>

<div>
    <p>Count: {{ $count }}</p>
    <button wire:click="increment">Increment</button>
</div>
```

> Key difference from class-style: use `state()` instead of declaring public properties. Actions are declared as arrow functions assigned to variables.

---

### 2. Props → Volt `state()` with External Values

**React:**

```jsx
function UserCard({ name, email }) {
    return (
        <div>
            <h2>{name}</h2>
            <p>{email}</p>
        </div>
    );
}
```

**Volt Inline:**

```php
<?php
use function Livewire\Volt\{state};

// Props passed from parent livewire component or route
state(['name' => '', 'email' => '']);
?>

<div>
    <h2>{{ $name }}</h2>
    <p>{{ $email }}</p>
</div>
```

**Blade component for pure display (no server state needed):**

```php
{{-- resources/views/components/user-card.blade.php --}}
@props(['name', 'email'])

<div>
    <h2>{{ $name }}</h2>
    <p>{{ $email }}</p>
</div>
```

```blade
{{-- Usage --}}
<x-user-card name="John" email="john@example.com" />
```

---

### 3. Component with Layout

**React:**

```jsx
function HomePage() {
    return (
        <Layout>
            <main>Home content</main>
        </Layout>
    );
}
```

**Volt Inline:**

```php
<?php
use function Livewire\Volt\{layout};

layout('components.layouts.app');
?>

<main>Home content</main>
```

