## State Management

### useState → state()

**React:**

```jsx
const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
const [items, setItems] = useState([]);
const [name, setName] = useState('');
```

**Volt Inline:**

```php
<?php
use function Livewire\Volt\{state};

state([
    'isOpen' => false,
    'items'  => [],
    'name'   => '',
]);
?>
```

---

### useEffect (on mount) → mount()

**React:**

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
    fetchItems().then(setItems);
}, []);
```

**Volt Inline:**

```php
<?php
use function Livewire\Volt\{state, mount};
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Log;

state(['items' => []]);

mount(function () {
    try {
        $file = public_path('media/json/items.json');
        $this->items = json_decode(file_get_contents($file), true) ?? [];
    } catch (\Throwable $e) {
        Log::warning('Failed to load items: ' . $e->getMessage());
        $this->items = [];
    }
});
?>
```

---

### useEffect with Dependency → on()

**React:**

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
    recalculate();
}, [selectedItem]);
```

**Volt Inline:**

```php
<?php
use function Livewire\Volt\{state, on};

state(['selectedItem' => null, 'total' => 0]);

on(['selectedItem' => function () {
    $this->total = computeTotal($this->selectedItem);
}]);
?>
```

> For property-watching within the component itself, define an `updated` function:

```php
$updatedSelectedItem = fn() => $this->total = computeTotal($this->selectedItem);
```

---

### useMemo → computed()

**React:**

```jsx
const total = useMemo(() => {
    return items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.price, 0);
}, [items]);
```

**Volt Inline:**

```php
<?php
use function Livewire\Volt\{state, computed};

state(['items' => []]);

$total = computed(fn() => collect($this->items)->sum('price'));
?>

{{-- In template --}}
<p>Total: {{ $this->total }}</p>
```

