## Data Fetching

### Client fetch() → PHP mount()

**React:**

```jsx
const [products, setProducts] = useState([]);

useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/products').then(res => res.json()).then(setProducts);
}, []);
```

**Volt Inline:**

```php
<?php
use function Livewire\Volt\{state, mount};
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Log;

state(['products' => []]);

mount(function () {
    try {
        // Option 1: JSON file (prototyping)
        $path = public_path('media/json/products.json');
        $this->products = json_decode(file_get_contents($path), true) ?? [];

        // Option 2: Database (production)
        // $this->products = \App\Models\Product::all()->toArray();
    } catch (\Throwable $e) {
        Log::error('Products load failed: ' . $e->getMessage());
        $this->products = [];
    }
});
?>
```

