## Common Patterns

### Conditional Rendering

**React:**

```jsx
{isLoading ? <Spinner /> : <Content />}
{items.length > 0 && <List />}
```

**Blade:**

```blade
@if($isLoading)
    <x-spinner />
@else
    <x-content />
@endif

@if(count($items) > 0)
    <x-list :items="$items" />
@endif
```

---

### Loops with Key

**React:**

```jsx
{products.map(product => (
    <ProductCard key={product.id} product={product} />
))}
```

**Blade:**

```blade
@foreach($products as $product)
    <div wire:key="product-{{ $product['id'] }}">
        <x-product-card :product="$product" />
    </div>
@endforeach
```

---

### Client-Only Toggle (React State → Alpine.js)

For UI-only state (dropdowns, modals, tabs) that never needs to reach the server, use Alpine.js instead of Livewire to avoid unnecessary round trips.

**React:**

```jsx
const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);

return (
    <div>
        <button onClick={() => setIsOpen(!isOpen)}>Toggle</button>
        {isOpen && <div>Content</div>}
    </div>
);
```

**Alpine.js in Blade:**

```blade
<div x-data="{ isOpen: false }">
    <button @click="isOpen = !isOpen">Toggle</button>
    <div x-show="isOpen" x-transition>Content</div>
</div>
```

---

### Two-Way Binding

**React:**

```jsx
<input value={search} onChange={e => setSearch(e.target.value)} />
```

**Blade:**

```blade
{{-- Debounced to avoid a request on every keystroke --}}
<input wire:model.live.debounce.300ms="search" type="text" />
```

---

### Named Slots

**React:**

```jsx
<Layout header={<Header />}>
    <Content />
</Layout>
```

**Blade:**

```blade
<x-layouts.app>
    <x-slot:header>
        <x-header />
    </x-slot:header>

    <x-content />
</x-layouts.app>
```

